analysis.info:
Fit a general time reversible model to a collection
    of training protein sequence alignments. Generate substitution
    and scoring matrices following the procedures described in Nickle et al 2007
analysis.citation: Nickle DC, Heath L, Jensen MA, Gilbert PB, Mullins JI, Kosakovsky Pond SL (2007) HIV-Specific Probabilistic Models of Protein Evolution. PLoS ONE 2(6): e503. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0000503
analysis.authors: Sergei L Kosakovsky Pond and Stephanie J Spielman
